# Gradle Commands Outside Sandbox

When running `./gradlew` commands that require network access or process spawning, ALWAYS use the `required_permissions: ["full_network"]` or `["all"]` parameter with the Shell tool.

## Examples

```kotlin
// Running gradle compile (needs full_network)
Shell(
    command = "./gradlew :domain:compileKotlin",
    required_permissions = ["full_network"],
    block_until_ms = 300000,
)

// Running gradle tests (needs full_network)
Shell(
    command = "./gradlew :domain:test",
    required_permissions = ["full_network"],
    block_until_ms = 300000,
)

// Running assembleDebug (needs full_network)
Shell(
    command = "./gradlew assembleDebug",
    required_permissions = ["full_network"],
    block_until_ms = 600000,
)
```

## Why This Is Needed

The sandbox restricts process spawning and network access. Gradle wrapper downloads dependencies and spawns JVM processes, which require permissions outside the sandbox. Without `required_permissions`, commands will fail with "Operation not permitted" or network errors.
